	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I think the usual way is to solder a resistor between two pins on the expansion port. Then you just connect one of the audio pins on the Famicom cartridge to the expansion input pin. The resistor value is correct though. <br /><br />I imagine that adapter will work just fine.

		

